  <Name>k__BackingField: Amos
  fancyName: 
  nickname: amo
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: bd3f8ba6a2445b646991a3e44f7f687a, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God and the Nations'
      title: God and the Nations
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Amos, who was among the herdmen of Tekoa, which he
        saw concerning Israel in the days of Uzziah king of Judah, and in the days
        of Jeroboam the son of Joash king of Israel, two years before the earthquake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Damascus'
      title: Damascus
      number: 2
      content: 'And he said, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> will roar from Zion,
        and utter his voice from Jerusalem; and the habitations of the shepherds
        shall mourn, and the top of Carmel shall wither.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; For three transgressions
        of Damascus, and for four, I will not turn away <i>the punishment</i> thereof;
        because they have threshed Gilead with threshing instruments of iron: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but I will send a fire into the house of Hazael, which shall devour
        the palaces of Ben-hadad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Gaza'
      title: Gaza
      number: 5
      content: 'I will break also the bar of Damascus, and cut off the inhabitant
        from the plain of Aven, and him that holdeth the sceptre from the house of
        Eden: and the people of Syria shall go into captivity unto Kir, saith the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; For three transgressions
        of Gaza, and for four, I will not turn away <i>the punishment</i> thereof;
        because they carried away captive the whole captivity, to deliver <i>them</i>
        up to Edom: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but I will send a fire on the wall of Gaza, which shall devour the
        palaces thereof: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Tyre'
      title: Tyre
      number: 8
      content: 'and I will cut off the inhabitant from Ashdod, and him that holdeth
        the sceptre from Ashkelon, and I will turn mine hand against Ekron: and the
        remnant of the Philistines shall perish, saith the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; For three transgressions
        of Tyrus, and for four, I will not turn away <i>the punishment</i> thereof;
        because they delivered up the whole captivity to Edom, and remembered not
        the brotherly covenant: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Edom'
      title: Edom
      number: 10
      content: 'but I will send a fire on the wall of Tyrus, which shall devour the
        palaces thereof.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; For three transgressions
        of Edom, and for four, I will not turn away <i>the punishment</i> thereof;
        because he did pursue his brother with the sword, and did cast off all pity,
        and his anger did tear perpetually, and he kept his wrath for ever: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Ammon'
      title: Ammon
      number: 12
      content: 'but I will send a fire upon Teman, which shall devour the palaces
        of Bozrah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; For three transgressions
        of the children of Ammon, and for four, I will not turn away <i>the punishment</i>
        thereof; because they have ripped up the women with child of Gilead, that
        they might enlarge their border: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but I will kindle a fire in the wall of Rabbah, and it shall devour
        the palaces thereof, with shouting in the day of battle, with a tempest in
        the day of the whirlwind: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: and their king shall go into captivity, he and his princes together,
        saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moab'
      title: Moab
      number: 1
      content: '  Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; For three transgressions
        of Moab, and for four, I will not turn away <i>the punishment</i> thereof;
        because he burned the bones of the king of Edom into lime: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'but I will send a fire upon Moab, and it shall devour the palaces
        of Kirioth: and Moab shall die with tumult, with shouting, <i>and</i> with
        the sound of the trumpet: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Judah'
      title: Judah
      number: 3
      content: 'and I will cut off the judge from the midst thereof, and will slay
        all the princes thereof with him, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; For three transgressions
        of Judah, and for four, I will not turn away <i>the punishment</i> thereof;
        because they have despised the law of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and
        have not kept his commandments, and their lies caused them to err, after
        the which their fathers have walked: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Israel'
      title: Israel
      number: 5
      content: 'but I will send a fire upon Judah, and it shall devour the palaces
        of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; For three transgressions
        of Israel, and for four, I will not turn away <i>the punishment</i> thereof;
        because they sold the righteous for silver, and the poor for a pair of shoes; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'that pant after the dust of the earth on the head of the poor, and
        turn aside the way of the meek: and a man and his father will go in unto
        the <i>same</i> maid, to profane my holy name: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and they lay <i>themselves</i> down upon clothes laid to pledge by
        every altar, and they drink the wine of the condemned <i>in</i> the house
        of their god.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Yet destroyed I the Amorite before them, whose height <i>was</i>
        like the height of the cedars, and he <i>was</i> strong as the oaks; yet
        I destroyed his fruit from above, and his roots from beneath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Also I brought you up from the land of Egypt, and led you forty years
        through the wilderness, to possess the land of the Amorite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I raised up of your sons for prophets, and of your young men
        for Nazarites. <i>Is it</i> not even thus, O ye children of Israel? saith
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But ye gave the Nazarites wine to drink; and commanded the prophets,
        saying, Prophesy not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold, I am pressed under you, as a cart is pressed <i>that is</i>
        full of sheaves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the flight shall perish from the swift, and the strong
        shall not strengthen his force, neither shall the mighty deliver himself: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'neither shall he stand that handleth the bow; and <i>he that is</i>
        swift of foot shall not deliver <i>himself:</i> neither shall he that rideth
        the horse deliver himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And <i>he that is</i> courageous among the mighty shall flee away
        naked in that day, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God and Israel'
      title: God and Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear this word that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath spoken
        against you, O children of Israel, against the whole family which I brought
        up from the land of Egypt, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You only have I known of all the families of the earth: therefore
        I will punish you for all your iniquities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Can two walk together, except they be agreed? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Will a lion roar in the forest, when he hath no prey? will a young
        lion cry out of his den, if he have taken nothing?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Can a bird fall in a snare upon the earth, where no gin <i>is</i>
        for him? shall <i>one</i> take up a snare from the earth, and have taken
        nothing at all? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Shall a trumpet be blown in the city, and the people not be afraid?
        shall there be evil in a city, and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath not
        done <i>it?</i>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Surely the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps> will do nothing, but he
        revealeth his secret unto his servants the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The lion hath roared, who will not fear? the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>
        hath spoken, who can but prophesy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Publish in the palaces at Ashdod, and in the palaces in the land
        of Egypt, and say, Assemble yourselves upon the mountains of Samaria, and
        behold the great tumults in the midst thereof, and the oppressed in the midst
        thereof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For they know not to do right, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        who store up violence and robbery in their palaces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore thus saith the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>; An adversary
        <i>there shall be</i> even round about the land; and he shall bring down
        thy strength from thee, and thy palaces shall be spoiled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; As the shepherd taketh
        out of the mouth of the lion two legs, or a piece of an ear; so shall the
        children of Israel be taken out that dwell in Samaria in the corner of a
        bed, and in Damascus <i>in</i> a couch.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hear ye, and testify in the house of Jacob, saith the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>,
        the God of hosts, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'that in the day that I shall visit the transgressions of Israel upon
        him I will also visit the altars of Beth-el: and the horns of the altar shall
        be cut off, and fall to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And I will smite the winter house with the summer house; and the houses
        of ivory shall perish, and the great houses shall have an end, saith the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Women of Samaria'
      title: The Women of Samaria
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear this word, ye kine of Bashan, that <i>are</i> in the mountain
        of Samaria, which oppress the poor, which crush the needy, which say to their
        masters, Bring, and let us drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps> hath sworn by his holiness, that,
        lo, the days shall come upon you, that he will take you away with hooks,
        and your posterity with fishhooks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And ye shall go out at the breaches, every <i>cow at that which is</i>
        before her; and ye shall cast <i>them</i> into the palace, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Come to Beth-el, and transgress; at Gilgal multiply transgression;
        and bring your sacrifices every morning, <i>and</i> your tithes after three
        years: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving with leaven, and proclaim <i>and</i>
        publish the free offerings: for this liketh you, O ye children of Israel,
        saith the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And I also have given you cleanness of teeth in all your cities,
        and want of bread in all your places: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And also I have withholden the rain from you, when <i>there were</i>
        yet three months to the harvest: and I caused it to rain upon one city, and
        caused it not to rain upon another city: one piece was rained upon, and the
        piece whereupon it rained not withered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So two <i>or</i> three cities wandered unto one city, to drink water;
        but they were not satisfied: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I have smitten you with blasting and mildew: when your gardens and
        your vineyards and your fig trees and your olive trees increased, the palmerworm
        devoured <i>them:</i> yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I have sent among you the pestilence after the manner of Egypt: your
        young men have I slain with the sword, and have taken away your horses; and
        I have made the stink of your camps to come up unto your nostrils: yet have
        ye not returned unto me, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I have overthrown <i>some</i> of you, as God overthrew Sodom and
        Gomorrah, and ye were as a firebrand plucked out of the burning: yet have
        ye not returned unto me, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore thus will I do unto thee, O Israel: <i>and</i> because
        I will do this unto thee, prepare to meet thy God, O Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For, lo, he that formeth the mountains, and createth the wind, and
        declareth unto man what <i>is</i> his thought, that maketh the morning darkness,
        and treadeth upon the high places of the earth, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        The God of hosts, <i>is</i> his name.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Worshippers of Beth-el'
      title: The Worshippers of Beth-el
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear ye this word which I take up against you, <i>even</i> a lamentation,
        O house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The virgin of Israel is fallen; she shall no more rise: she is forsaken
        upon her land; <i>there is</i> none to raise her up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For thus saith the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>; The city that
        went out <i>by</i> a thousand shall leave an hundred, and that which went
        forth <i>by</i> an hundred shall leave ten, to the house of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> unto the house of
        Israel, Seek ye me, and ye shall live: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'but seek not Beth-el, nor enter into Gilgal, and pass not to Beer-sheba:
        for Gilgal shall surely go into captivity, and Beth-el shall come to nought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Seek the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and ye shall live; lest he
        break out like fire in the house of Joseph, and devour <i>it</i>, and <i>there
        be</i> none to quench <i>it</i> in Beth-el. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Ye who turn judgment to wormwood, and leave off righteousness in
        the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<i>seek him</i> that maketh the seven stars and Orion, and turneth
        the shadow of death into the morning, and maketh the day dark with night:
        that calleth for the waters of the sea, and poureth them out upon the face
        of the earth: The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> his name: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'that strengtheneth the spoiled against the strong, so that the spoiled
        shall come against the fortress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They hate him that rebuketh in the gate, and they abhor him that
        speaketh uprightly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Forasmuch therefore as your treading <i>is</i> upon the poor, and
        ye take from him burdens of wheat: ye have built houses of hewn stone, but
        ye shall not dwell in them; ye have planted pleasant vineyards, but ye shall
        not drink wine of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For I know your manifold transgressions and your mighty sins: they
        afflict the just, they take a bribe, and they turn aside the poor in the
        gate <i>from their right</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore the prudent shall keep silence in that time; for it <i>is</i>
        an evil time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Seek good, and not evil, that ye may live: and so the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        the God of hosts, shall be with you, as ye have spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Hate the evil, and love the good, and establish judgment in the gate:
        it may be that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of hosts will be gracious
        unto the remnant of Joseph.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, the God of hosts, the
        Lord, saith thus; Wailing <i>shall be</i> in all streets; and they shall
        say in all the highways, Alas! alas! and they shall call the husbandman to
        mourning, and such as are skilful of lamentation to wailing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And in all vineyards <i>shall be</i> wailing: for I will pass through
        thee, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Woe unto you that desire the day of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>!
        to what end <i>is</i> it for you? the day of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>is</i> darkness, and not light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'As if a man did flee from a lion, and a bear met him; or went into
        the house, and leaned his hand on the wall, and a serpent bit him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<i>Shall</i> not the day of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>be</i>
        darkness, and not light? even very dark, and no brightness in it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I hate, I despise your feast days, and I will not smell in your solemn
        assemblies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Though ye offer me burnt offerings and your meat offerings, I will
        not accept <i>them:</i> neither will I regard the peace offerings of your
        fat beasts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Take thou away from me the noise of thy songs; for I will not hear
        the melody of thy viols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But let judgment run down as waters, and righteousness as a mighty
        stream.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Have ye offered unto me sacrifices and offerings in the wilderness
        forty years, O house of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But ye have borne the tabernacle of your Moloch and Chiun your images,
        the star of your god, which ye made to yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Therefore will I cause you to go into captivity beyond Damascus, saith
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, whose name <i>is</i> The God of hosts.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Rulers at Ease'
      title: The Rulers at Ease
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe to them <i>that are</i> at ease in Zion, and trust in the mountain
        of Samaria, <i>which are</i> named chief of the nations, to whom the house
        of Israel came! '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Pass ye unto Calneh, and see; and from thence go ye to Hamath the
        great: then go down to Gath of the Philistines: <i>be they</i> better than
        these kingdoms? or their border greater than your border? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Ye that put far away the evil day, and cause the seat of violence
        to come near; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'that lie upon beds of ivory, and stretch themselves upon their couches,
        and eat the lambs out of the flock, and the calves out of the midst of the
        stall; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'that chant to the sound of the viol, <i>and</i> invent to themselves
        instruments of musick, like David; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'that drink wine in bowls, and anoint themselves with the chief ointments:
        but they are not grieved for the affliction of Joseph.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore now shall they go captive with the first that go captive,
        and the banquet of them that stretched themselves shall be removed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps> hath sworn by himself, saith
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> the God of hosts, I abhor the excellency
        of Jacob, and hate his palaces: therefore will I deliver up the city with
        all that is therein. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, if there remain ten men in one house,
        that they shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And a man''s uncle shall take him up, and he that burneth him, to
        bring out the bones out of the house, and shall say unto him that <i>is</i>
        by the sides of the house, <i>Is there</i> yet <i>any</i> with thee? and
        he shall say, No. Then shall he say, Hold thy tongue: for we may not make
        mention of the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For, behold, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> commandeth, and he will
        smite the great house with breaches, and the little house with clefts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Shall horses run upon the rock? will <i>one</i> plow <i>there</i>
        with oxen? for ye have turned judgment into gall, and the fruit of righteousness
        into hemlock: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'ye which rejoice in a thing of nought, which say, Have we not taken
        to us horns by our own strength? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: But, behold, I will raise up against you a nation, O house of Israel,
        saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> the God of hosts; and they shall afflict
        you from the entering in of Hemath unto the river of the wilderness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Visions of JudgementLocusts'
      title: Visions of JudgementLocusts
      number: 1
      content: '  Thus hath the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps> shewed unto me; and,
        behold, he formed grasshoppers in the beginning of the shooting up of the
        latter growth; and, lo, <i>it was</i> the latter growth after the king''s
        mowings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it came to pass, <i>that</i> when they had made an end of eating
        the grass of the land, then I said, O Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>, forgive,
        I beseech thee: by whom shall Jacob arise? for he <i>is</i> small. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Fire'
      title: Fire
      number: 3
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> repented for this: It shall not be,
        saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus hath the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps> shewed unto me: and,
        behold, the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps> called to contend by fire, and
        it devoured the great deep, and did eat up a part. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then said I, O Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>, cease, I beseech
        thee: by whom shall Jacob arise? for he <i>is</i> small. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Plumbline'
      title: The Plumbline
      number: 6
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> repented for this: This also shall
        not be, saith the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Thus he shewed me: and, behold, the Lord stood upon a wall <i>made</i>
        by a plumbline, with a plumbline in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto me, Amos, what seest
        thou? And I said, A plumbline. Then said the Lord, Behold, I will set a plumbline
        in the midst of my people Israel: I will not again pass by them any more: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Amos at Beth-el'
      title: Amos at Beth-el
      number: 9
      content: 'and the high places of Isaac shall be desolate, and the sanctuaries
        of Israel shall be laid waste; and I will rise against the house of Jeroboam
        with the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Amaziah the priest of Beth-el sent to Jeroboam king of Israel,
        saying, Amos hath conspired against thee in the midst of the house of Israel:
        the land is not able to bear all his words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For thus Amos saith, Jeroboam shall die by the sword, and Israel
        shall surely be led away captive out of their own land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Also Amaziah said unto Amos, O thou seer, go, flee thee away into
        the land of Judah, and there eat bread, and prophesy there: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'but prophesy not again any more at Beth-el: for it <i>is</i> the
        king''s chapel, and it <i>is</i> the king''s court.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then answered Amos, and said to Amaziah, I <i>was</i> no prophet,
        neither <i>was</i> I a prophet''s son; but I <i>was</i> an herdman, and a
        gatherer of sycomore fruit: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> took me as I followed the flock,
        and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto me, Go, prophesy unto my people
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now therefore hear thou the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        Thou sayest, Prophesy not against Israel, and drop not <i>thy word</i> against
        the house of Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; Thy wife shall
        be an harlot in the city, and thy sons and thy daughters shall fall by the
        sword, and thy land shall be divided by line; and thou shalt die in a polluted
        land: and Israel shall surely go into captivity forth of his land.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Basket of Fruit'
      title: A Basket of Fruit
      number: 1
      content: '  Thus hath the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps> shewed unto me: and
        behold a basket of summer fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he said, Amos, what seest thou? And I said, A basket of summer
        fruit. Then said the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> unto me, The end is come
        upon my people of Israel; I will not again pass by them any more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the songs of the temple shall be howlings in that day, saith
        the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>: <i>there shall be</i> many dead bodies
        in every place; they shall cast <i>them</i> forth with silence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear this, O ye that swallow up the needy, even to make the poor
        of the land to fail, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'saying, When will the new moon be gone, that we may sell corn? and
        the sabbath, that we may set forth wheat, making the ephah small, and the
        shekel great, and falsifying the balances by deceit? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'That we may buy the poor for silver, and the needy for a pair of
        shoes; <i>yea</i>, and sell the refuse of the wheat? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath sworn by the excellency of Jacob,
        Surely I will never forget any of their works. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Shall not the land tremble for this, and every one mourn that dwelleth
        therein? and it shall rise up wholly as a flood; and it shall be cast out
        and drowned, as <i>by</i> the flood of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>,
        that I will cause the sun to go down at noon, and I will darken the earth
        in the clear day: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and I will turn your feasts into mourning, and all your songs into
        lamentation; and I will bring up sackcloth upon all loins, and baldness upon
        every head; and I will make it as the mourning of an only <i>son</i>, and
        the end thereof as a bitter day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, the days come, saith the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>,
        that I will send a famine in the land, not a famine of bread, nor a thirst
        for water, but of hearing the words of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and they shall wander from sea to sea, and from the north even to
        the east, they shall run to and fro to seek the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and shall not find <i>it</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In that day shall the fair virgins and young men faint for thirst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They that swear by the sin of Samaria, and say, Thy god, O Dan, liveth;
        and, The manner of Beer-sheba liveth; even they shall fall, and never rise
        up again.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Lord at the Altar'
      title: The Lord at the Altar
      number: 1
      content: '  I saw the Lord standing upon the altar: and he said, Smite the
        lintel of the door, that the posts may shake: and cut them in the head, all
        of them; and I will slay the last of them with the sword: he that fleeth
        of them shall not flee away, and he that escapeth of them shall not be delivered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Though they dig into hell, thence shall mine hand take them; though
        they climb up to heaven, thence will I bring them down: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and though they hide themselves in the top of Carmel, I will search
        and take them out thence; and though they be hid from my sight in the bottom
        of the sea, thence will I command the serpent, and he shall bite them: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and though they go into captivity before their enemies, thence will
        I command the sword, and it shall slay them: and I will set mine eyes upon
        them for evil, and not for good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps> of hosts <i>is</i> he that
        toucheth the land, and it shall melt, and all that dwell therein shall mourn:
        and it shall rise up wholly like a flood; and shall be drowned, as <i>by</i>
        the flood of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<i>It is</i> he that buildeth his stories in the heaven, and hath
        founded his troop in the earth; he that calleth for the waters of the sea,
        and poureth them out upon the face of the earth: The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>is</i> his name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  <i>Are</i> ye not as children of the Ethiopians unto me, O children
        of Israel? saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. Have not I brought up Israel
        out of the land of Egypt? and the Philistines from Caphtor, and the Syrians
        from Kir? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Behold, the eyes of the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>  <i>are</i>
        upon the sinful kingdom, and I will destroy it from off the face of the earth;
        saving that I will not utterly destroy the house of Jacob, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For, lo, I will command, and I will sift the house of Israel among
        all nations, like as <i>corn</i> is sifted in a sieve, yet shall not the
        least grain fall upon the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All the sinners of my people shall die by the sword, which say, The
        evil shall not overtake nor prevent us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In that day will I raise up the tabernacle of David that is fallen,
        and close up the breaches thereof; and I will raise up his ruins, and I will
        build it as in the days of old: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'that they may possess the remnant of Edom, and of all the heathen,
        which are called by my name, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> that doeth
        this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold, the days come, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, that
        the plowman shall overtake the reaper, and the treader of grapes him that
        soweth seed; and the mountains shall drop sweet wine, and all the hills shall
        melt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And I will bring again the captivity of my people of Israel, and
        they shall build the waste cities, and inhabit <i>them</i>; and they shall
        plant vineyards, and drink the wine thereof; they shall also make gardens,
        and eat the fruit of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And I will plant them upon their land, and they shall no more be pulled
        up out of their land which I have given them, saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        thy God.
      comments: []
